-- Italy's Carige says rights issue 99.9 pct subscribed
-- By Danilo Masoni
-- Fri Jul 04, 2014 12:50PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 4 (Reuters) - Italian mid-sized lender Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> said on Friday it had raised 798.2 million euros ($1.09 billion) in a rights issue, strengthening its balance sheet ahead of a European review of banking assets.

In a statement, the Genoa-based lender said the highly-dilutive share sale was 99.9 percent subscribed, adding that unsubscribed rights will be offered on the market July 8-14.